<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1029" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1029">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1845:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1029<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1029fn1">Printed from the text received in the Department of
                                    State.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18">July 18, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Victory1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi></gloss>
                                68. For Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>,
                                London, repeated to State Department, Washington from Secretary of
                                State, Berlin.</p>
                            <p>U. S. and <gloss target="#t_UK1">U. K.</gloss> military authorities
                                in Germany agree that French Berlin area of occupation will be
                                formed from existing <gloss target="#t_UK1">U. K.</gloss> and U. S.
                                areas.</p>
                            <p>As soon as <gloss target="#t_UK1">U. K.</gloss> representative <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss><note n="2" xml:id="d1029fn2"><persName corresp="#p_CSRI1">Sir Ronald I.
                                        Campbell</persName>.</note> have [<hi rend="italic">has</hi>] received similar instructions, you are authorized accept
                                Soviet July 12th [<hi rend="italic">11th</hi>] proposal<note n="3" xml:id="d1029fn3">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d411">vol.
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, document No.
                                    411</ref>.</note> for final sentence report accompanying
                                agreement on French Zone in Germany and conclude agreement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_OCT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>